    "content": "1. Gradient의 의미 등위선 또는 등위면에서 법선(수직) 뱡향의 기울기 이다.\n2. Gradient for scalar 매개변수 공간 → 실공간 직교좌표계\n$$\r\\nabla_u\r:=\\hat{u}_j\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial u_j} \\implies\r\\nabla\r:=\\hat{e}_j\\frac{\\partial}{h_j\\partial u_j}\r$$ 데카르트좌표계: $$\\hat{u}_1=\\hat{u}_x, \\hat{u}_2=\\hat{u}_y, \\hat{u}_3=\\hat{u}_z$$$$h_1=1, h_2=1, h_3=1$$$$\\hat{e}_1=\\hat{x}, \\hat{e}_2=\\hat{y}, \\hat{e}_3=\\hat{z}$$ 원통좌표계: $$\\hat{u}_1=\\hat{u}_\\rho, \\hat{u}_2=\\hat{u}_\\phi, \\hat{u}_3=\\hat{u}_z$$$$h_1=1, h_2=\\rho, h_3=1$$$$\\hat{e}_1=\\hat{\\rho}, \\hat{e}_2=\\hat{\\phi}, \\hat{e}_3=\\hat{z}$$ 구좌표계: $$\\hat{u}_1=\\hat{u}_r, \\hat{u}_2=\\hat{u}_\\theta, \\hat{u}_3=\\hat{u}_\\phi$$$$h_1=1, h_2=r, h_3=r\\sin\\theta$$$$\\hat{e}_1=\\hat{r}, \\hat{e}_2=\\hat{\\theta}, \\hat{e}_3=\\hat{\\phi}$$ Gradient - 위키백과, 우리 모두의 백과사전",
